## The Bigger Picture

Active gaming isn't a niche. It's where entertainment is heading.

Physical movement, digital immersion, social competition, shareable moments — it hits every note modern audiences are looking for. It works for a birthday, a rainy Saturday, a corporate event, or a spontaneous Tuesday night when you want to do something real.

Passive entertainment had a long run. Active gaming is what's next.

